Two Americans escaped the Malaysian hostage situation in Sabah, where most captives were Europeans and Americans.
The kidnappers, believed to be Filipinos, took the hostages onto a boat at sea.
The Murphys, an American couple, evaded capture by hiding in bushes.
The Philippine military is investigating the involvement of Abu Sayyaf rebels.
A group of vigilantes retaliated by seizing Abu Sayyaf leader's relatives.
Malaysian and Philippine authorities are coordinating efforts to rescue the hostages, mostly foreign tourists.
The situation remains tense as authorities work to secure the captives' release.
